result.name: 正宗山西刀削麵皇 (沙咀道)

reviews.text: Hand cut noodles, a bit too doughy but fine as a neighborhood noodle shop. Friendly service. Gets pretty busy so if you go at peak meal times, be prepared to queue. (The foods not really worth queuing for though).
Nice food, crowded seats

好夠辣嘅餸，中意牛腩湯低，獨有嘅味道，但係唔知有冇落味精，次次食完都好口渴
I love the side dishes there.They are very spicy and tasty.Good for people who love spicy foods.But I think they might have added a lots MSG to the soup because I felt very thirsty after eating this.

A famous noodles shop around the area, it got another branch nearby. You could always find a queue outside during peak hours. The term "刀削麵 knife-shaved noodles" mean the noodles are made by shaving off the dough using a knife. You would definitely love the texture if you are a lover for chewy Chinese noodles. Yet it's a bit pricey when compared to other local noodles shop.
Famous noodles chain restaurant in Hong Kong, and this particular shop is the best of them all. Highly recommended to visit this shop if you really try that out.

reviews.text: 薄味でクセのないスープと食べ応えのある刀削麺は初めての方でも楽しめるかと、麺に厚みがあるので注文から提供まで時間が掛かるのでその間はサイドメニューを頼んで楽しむのが良い。パクチーが苦手な方は必ず全部の料理でパクチーを抜くことを忘れずに！ オススメは刀削担々麺enjoy！
生意太好，要兩人逼在卡位一邊，吃得很辛苦。五香牛肉、豬軟骨都很有水準，但刀削麵口感實在太差，亦比較重味。份量夠吃得飽，價錢中上不算便宜，繁忙時段需要排隊。
荃灣沙咀道 好食 但係多味精 坐位又坐得唔舒服 食過兩次就冇去
乾拌刀削麵才能吃出刀削紮實彈牙的口感, 美味的醬汁配上一杯凍飲實在極好😄
無食過，但每次路過都幾多人
